cs.CY, cs.HC, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.LG 

This paper discusses the design and implementation of data dividends, which involves the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. The focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and the need to distribute the economic benefits of AI technologies suggests that cs.CY (Computers and Society) is the most likely category. The use of algorithms and datasets to simulate the effects of different design decisions points to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as likely categories. Finally, the consideration of demographic disparities and the need for cautious design decisions suggest that cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also a relevant category.
